Exploring the iris dataset¶

This notebook demonstrates basic features of latentspaceexplorer on the iris dataset.

Make sure you have started a Redis Database instance with:

make start-redis

from lse import LatentSpaceInterface
from sklearn.datasets import load_iris

import pandas as pd

iris_data = load_iris(as_frame=True)

We convert target to string for discrete colormapping, and start the app on port 8050:

import logging

logger = logging.getLogger()
logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)
logging.debug("test")

2024-10-12 16:43:34 - root - DEBUG: test

app = LatentSpaceInterface(
    pd.concat((iris_data["data"], iris_data["target"].astype(str)), axis=1),
    dashboard_title="Iris Data Exploration",
    port=8050,
).start()

Import tab¶

We use all features to initialize the pipeline. We set the number of clusters to 3.

Explore tab¶

  • The dataset is best fitted with 2 components from a bayesian criterium standpoint.

  • The boundary between Versicolor and Virginia species is a fine line in TSNE space.

Export Tab¶

The export tab let you sort the data according to their log probability, highlighting different anomaly patterns:

  • 1 very big virginica flower.

  • 1 versicolor flower with small petal length and petal width.

  • 2 tiny setosa flowers.
